    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just read your wonderful article in bon appetit on making mixed berry jam, which led me to your blog- what a great find for me!</></>One question with the jam, can you substitute honey for the sugar? same quantity of honey as sugar?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1727#comment-2662' data-commentid="2662" data-postid="1727" data-belowelement="comment-2662" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to jenn" aria-label='Reply to jenn'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-2663" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Corrie</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=1727#comment-2663"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-04-26T17:53:00-04:00">Sunday, April 26, 2009 at 5:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly,<br />I am from Germany. I discovered your blog some weeks ago and am reading my way through from the beginning. It&#8217;s fun, and I keep on printing recipes madly. I even bought your book.<br />I&#8217;ve been cooking jam for years and always used the upside-down method with used jam jars, as mentioned in the other comments, (I don&#8217;t even sterilize them), and everyone I know does it, and it was described that way in every German jam recipe I ever saw. I think that&#8217;s much easier than special canning jars. And I can assure you, the jam keeps forever, too.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=1727#comment-2663' data-commentid="2663" data-postid="1727" data-belowelement="comment-2663" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Corrie" aria-label='Reply to Corrie'>Reply</a>    </div>
